Summer layering!
.
Mul cotton saree : @vilayaaclothing 
Block-print cape : @keva_design 
Blouse fabric : @itokri 
Neckpiece worn as belt : @creyons_ .
Just experimenting a bit with layering, inspired by the Emirati girls who wear 'Abayas' over their clothing. I've realized that layering isn't just a winter thing. Today, this cotton layering worked perfectly for me because the cape protected me from the sun, while I was out. I could easily remove it, while I was indoors and wear it again when the AC got uncomfortably cold. I should do this more often this summer. .
I love these hand-woven mul cotton sarees by @vilayaaclothing. They are not just light and soft but also stay in place, unlike some muls that don't retain shape after a few minutes of draping. .
The cape had come as a part of a dress-set. I used it today with the saree. To see how it looks with the dress, swipe away. 
For the previous avatars of the marigold print blouse, swipe till the end. I keep saying that cotton is my soul fabric. Hand-block printed cotton is definitely 'Nirvana' for my soul 😊 .

Self love is the greatest gift you can give to yourself. It doesn't just happen, its built over time just like any other love.

Its something that is learned through daily rituals, routines and practice. Its how you treat yourself, how you see yourself, what you believe of yourself, how you let others treat you and the boundaries you set of what you will and won't allow into your world.

Self love can also fade like any other love. So remember to treat yourself with kindness and respect daily and command the same from others. Monitor and change your thoughts, the self talk, the negative chatter. Rule of thumb:  If you wouldn't think or say it to someone you love, you shouldn't be saying it to yourself.

Self love is a life long journey...have you begun yours yet?

🥰We were created perfect.⠀
⠀
Sometime last week, the soul asked me...⠀
⠀
🤷‍♀️"Why do you want to be a better person?⠀
⠀
What's wrong with you now?"⠀
⠀
I was stumped by this question.

I sat with the questions and came to a  conclusion that there's nothing wrong with me.

Of course there's nothing with wanting more because life wants you to have more experiences and growth.⠀
⠀
🌌After all the Universe is Limitless.⠀
⠀
Therefore, we need to reframe our mind when we say "I want to be a better person."⠀
⠀
Because the underlying intention is that we're broken and we need to be fixed.⠀
⠀
(Unless it's not of course.)⠀
⠀
👸The whole reason why we're on this path to become the best and live the best versions of ourselves and reach our fullest potential (again it's limitless).⠀
⠀
Don't feel bad for not knowing soon or learning the lesson faster.

You're exactly where you need to be.⠀
⠀
No experiences are a waste of time.

It's part of you becoming who you're born to be.⠀
⠀
🙅‍♀️So stop wasting time wishing it didn't happen and this and that.

Seize the moment right now.⠀
⠀
🤹‍♀️Every moment counts.⠀
⠀
Enjoy the unfolding.⠀
⠀

Peri Peri Chicken
Follow @thebriskkitchen

Ingredients 
Cornflour - 2 tablespoons 
Maida - 2 tablespoons 
Salt - 1/2 teaspoon 
White pepper - 1/2 teaspoon 
Water - 50 ml
Chicken - 150 gm
Cooking oil - 150 ml
Cooking oil - 2 tablespoons 
Chopped garlic - 20 gm
Chopped ginger - 20 gm
Chopped onion - 10 gm
Chopped green chilli - 1
Water - 100 ml
White pepper - 1/2 teaspoon 
Salt - 1 tablespoon 
Red chilli sauce - 1 teaspoon 
Schezwan sauce - 2 tablespoons 
Peri peri sauce - 1 tablespoon 
Cornflour (1 tablespoon) mixed with Water (10 ml)
Chopped spring onion - 1 tablespoon 
Preparation 
In a mixing bowl add cornflour, maida, salt, white pepper and water. Mix well. Add the chicken pieces and mix well. Shallow fry the chicken till golden, and keep aside.
In a pan heat oil. Add chopped garlic, ginger, onion and green chilli. Sauté. Add water and mix well. Add white pepper, salt and red chilli sauce. Mix well. Add schezwan sauce and pei peri sauce. Mix well. Add cornflour+water mix and mix well. Add the fried chicken and chopped spring onion and mix gently.

Seyal Pav

Bored of Pav Maska? Here's how you can transform pav into this amazing zesty Seyal Pav.  Pav laao aur Seyal Pav Khao!
.
.
.
Seyal Pav
Ingredients:

Onion ½ Cup 
Tomato 1 Cup 
Garlic Cloves 7 
Coriander 1 Cup 
Green Chillies 3 
Ginger 1 Tbsp 
Water 
Oil 4 Tbsp 
Cumin Seeds 1 Tsp 
Curry Leaves 8 
Red Chilli Powder 1 Tsp 
Garam Masala 1 Tsp 
Turmeric Powder ½ Tsp 
Coriander Powder 1 Tsp 
Salt 
Water 
Pav 4 
Coriander 
Onion 
Sev 
Lemon 
Coriander 
Method:
Take a mixer and add the onion, tomato, garlic, coriander, green chilli, ginger and water. Make a paste like consistency of it.
Take a pan and add oil to it. Add cumin seeds, curry leaves and mix. 
Add the prepared paste and give it a good stir. 
Add in the red chilli powder, pav bhaji masala, turmeric powder, garam masala and salt and mix it well Add water and allow to boil.
Then add squared cut pav and mix well. Add coriander and mix well. Seyal pav is ready.
Serve it with chopped onion, sev ,lemon wedge and coriander.

Glacier Clinic - Tax Preparation Software
Wednesday, April 10 ● 3:30-4:30 PM ● 1202 Edward St. John
This workshop is for Nonresident Aliens for Tax Purposes only. It provides NRAs an overview of the US tax return filing process and assists with navigating Glacier Tax Prep in order to complete the 2018 tax return and Form 8843. These forms are required to be mailed to the Internal Revenue Service by the deadline of Monday, April 15, 2019
Things to bring to the workshop:
- Form W2
- Form 1042 (if you had a tax treaty and/or scholarships)
- Your laptop so you can log into Glacier Tax Prep during the workshop and complete your 2018 tax return
To gain access to Glacier Tax Prep software:
Log into your iTerp account at https://iterp.umd.edu .
Select Insurance and Finances > Glacier Tax Preparation.
Review instructions to ensure you have required documentation to begin the tax return filing process.
Click Access Glacier Tax Prep. You will be redirected to Arctic International's website to login using your Glacier account. If you do not have an existing account, you can create a new one.

Anchor-man ⚓ Exploring the island of Pulau Ubin was as refreshing as a change of scenery could possibly be in Singapore (I was a very schweeaty man in this heat 😅). The island was awesome because it had many traces of Singapore of the past - not as modern and built up as the mainland and other areas. We took to bikes which is the best way to get around the island; encountered monkeys, Singapore's tallest tree, and took a hike up to the island's best viewing point. My favourite part of the island was the main street, which was dotted with bike stalls and a couple of bars / restaurants. Really cool vibe 👌 #motionbros @singaporeair @visit_singapore #flysq #singaporesquad

Four moons passing in front of Saturn.

The large orange moon in front is Titan, followed by Mimas a little lower and to the left. 
Further to the left are Dione and the Enceladus. This transit, captured by Hubble, only happen once every 15 years, when Saturn's rings are tilted "edge on" from the point of view of Earth.

Video: NASA, ESA, and G. Bacon (STScI)

Your home should tell the story of your life and shelter the things you love. As part of a recent proposal we put together the 5 design principles that we live by at Studio North. 
1 . EQUALITY
Good design is for everyone, not just the privileged few. We’re enthusiastic about creating spaces for people to live meaningful and connected lives.

2. SUSTAINABILITY
The environment that surrounds us is a constant source of inspiration and influence for design. Taking the sun, the wind, and the landscape into consideration early in the design is important to our process.

3. CREATIVITY
Your home is an expression of who you are. We design homes that are not only a product of our creativity, but also allow for our clients to put their own touch on the space.

4. ACTIVITY
We believe that homes should be designed to suit the changing needs of today's families. As societal values shift and redefine notions of home, we listen and learn to how people want to live and design based on that foundation.

5. ECONOMY
Good design shouldn’t be needlessly expensive. While creating exceptional design, we intend to focus on simple, yet impactful spaces that are appreciated and attainable by everyone.

My take on the classic old Harry rocks shot. I think it's hard going to a place like this that has been photographed countless times by so many amazing photographers and trying to come away with something different , or something you feel happy with. I feel that although these popular places are incredible and it's a joy to photograph them, there is always some kind of pressure whilst you're there and during the editing process which can effect your creativity. All I would say is don't worry about being better than others or different but just do it for yourself, get lost in the moment and most of all enjoy it. If you can really let go in that moment, that's when the creative juices flow 😊
.
.
I think that a lot of the time it's the editing that sets photographers apart when looking at images from locations such as this, who agrees? Would love to hear your thoughts 👍

A weirdly communal feeling

Can I just be honest you all? It's been  more than a year and half since I started off with YouTube, and content creation has become such a buzz word. Everybody who's on social media, looks at their job like creation. Which it is. Even I have started thinking along those lines. Or rather I was thinking along those lines. .
.
.
It's all about perfectly curated experiences and photos and filters. But hear me out. I've never been the kind who would create a set or pose for a poolside picnic with a beautiful picnic basket et cetera. Not that it's bad, but just not my style. This day reminded me more so of how I love sharing experiences more than anything. I was sweaty post a long hike, my hair was messy, and I was extremely hungry. The driver who was with me in Paro, mr. Yonten got some home cooked Bhutanes lunch. He took me to a secret picnic location where locals usually go, and it was sooo perfect. We had a few dogs around us who were also just as hungry and ready to share the food. There were fluttering flags in the background and we had a bright, clear sky. Mr. Yonten was too amused when I set up my camera. But can you believe just how precious this moment was? This trip reminded me of the kind of "content" that comes naturally to me. Beautiful experiences amidst all the glory of nature, including human flaws. 😊

At Tokuda Hospital in Bulgaria, a patient has received one of the first 3D-printed ribs, as part of a life-saving operation.
Ivaylo Josifov was a healthy, active 35-year-old, who thought he had tonsillitis. However, an x-ray of his chest revealed a mass by one of his ribs, which turned out to be a congenital disease.This meant his rib needed replacing, as the disease could lead to breathing difficulties. 
Traditional implants are costly, as they are made from titanium, and aren’t perfect replicas. But now, a 3D-printed version is available and it’s much more cost effective.The labour, cost of materials and machine time combined cost less than 100 euros and the rib can be scanned and printed in less than 24 hours. Its properties are also more like a real rib than the usual titanium replacements.
Thanks to his new 3D printed rib, Josifov is now back to excellent health 💗

"Someday, sometime, you will be sitting somewhere. A berm overlooking a pond in Vermont. The lip of the Grand Canyon at sunset. A seat on the subway. And something bad will have happened: You will have lost someone you loved, or failed at something at which you badly wanted to succeed. And sitting there, you will fall into the center of yourself. You will look for some core to sustain you. And if you have been perfect all your life and have managed to meet all the expectations of your family, your friends, your community, your society, chances are excellent that there will be a black hole where that core ought to be. I don't want anyone I know to take that terrible chance. And the only way to avoid it is to listen to that small voice inside you that tells you to make mischief, to have fun, to be contrarian, to go another way. George Eliot wrote, 'It is never too late to be what you might have been.' It is never too early, either." —Anna Quindlen, Being Perfect

Staying hydrated has many benefits - like easy digestion, clearer skin, and pain-free Periods. Yes, if you want your Period to be less painful, drink water. If you feel bloated, drink water. If you feel tired and cranky, drink water. Because as the estrogen and progesterone levels in your body decline, your body starts retaining more water. And in doing so, it leaves you bloated, constipated, and causes gases. Drinking at least 8-10 glasses of water a day flushes out waste from your system, and fights bloating, thus reducing the severity of your cramps and enabling easy flow of period blood. So, HYDRATE HYDRATE HYDRATE. And do carry your own water bottle to reduce plastic usage.

I'd choose my orange bar (daily.. without fail) and would lick and slurp it. Ice cream - white, my tongue - orange..and I - a satisfied kid. Beauty Tip: "Onion on pigmentation"
.
Onion juice – Onions are a rich source of Vitamin C which is an amazing antioxidant and helps in treating pigmentation. Take a slice of red onion. ( Please avoid white onions). Rub the slice on the affected area of the skin.
.
.
💎You Will Need
•1 Fresh Red Onion .
.
💎Prep Time
2-5 minutes .
.
💎Treatment Time
10 minutes .
.
💎Method
1.Slice the red onion.
2.Take a slice and start rubbing the affected areas on your skin with it.
3.Wait for 10 minutes and then proceed to rinse with lukewarm water.
4.Optionally, you can grate the onion, squeeze out its juice, and apply the juice onto the affected area. .
.
.
💎How Often?
Twice a day until you notice improvement.
Why This Works
Onions are an excellent source of vitamin C, an antioxidant that can be used for treating pigmentation
.
.
.

Dear Instafamily,
This is my #saturdayselfie with food series number 20 ( can be a selfie 🤳or pic with food) ! It is with my favorite Vadapav from Ashok Vadapav near Kirti College in Mumbai ! 
Well , as is my  habit of multitasking,😛😜,I am also making this a gratitude post for 35K strong Instafamily!! Thank you thank you thank u!
Some of you will say but it’s 36 .7 k + ! Well a funny incident happened to me a few days ago! While my account was almost 35 k , overnight 4K plus followers were added to it! And no post was viral during that time! Now as lot of people told me the fake followers numbers will fall and they are thankfully ! It was so shocking but it can happen to any of us. 
I wrote to Instagram and also put in my stories ! It is the work of some demented mind and I was initially irritated! But then I thought , man I have become sort of important for someone to do so ! And that means I have arrived !! 😎😎And I am not going anywhere! Am here to stay and slay !! To scale the heights of success along with my slowly but steadily growing Instafamily! Yes numbers do matter to me ; they show me the level I can achieve ( besides brand endorsement and collabs😄🙊)! So all this crazy stuff encourages me more to keep doing what I love! 
Also wanted to share I am doing content writing too ( along with PR work and other stuff I was doing)and all these opportunities I got thanks to the love you guys showed on my posts and especially the captions!😊🤗😍. Thanks once again and god bless ! 🤗🤗😍❤️❤️.
Yours truly 
Geeta Hansaria

Какой должен быть базовый гардероб?
⠀
В моем гардеробе базовые вещи (те, с которыми можно сделать комбинации луков) в первую очередь должны быть удобными и лаконичными, чтобы с ними можно было сочетать все что угодно! Для меня это (особенно на весну):
⠀
▫️Белая футболка
Мужского кроя, которы идеально смотрится с джинсами, юбками и пиджаками ⠀
▫️Белая рубашка
Желательно over-size, чтобы в пир и в мир
⠀
▫️Джинсы

Hello everyone! This is a rotifer Synchaeta and it's my favorite rotifer genus. Look at tiny "flippers" on its sides. 😂 Ahhh it's such a cute gurl! I will name her Flipper because of the obvious reason.
.
There are so many other rotifers from genus Kretalla in the video, they keep bumping into Flipper and scaring her. Rotifers are tiny microscopic animals and they have muscles, stomachs and even "brains".
.
I remember that I got so excited when I first spotted Flipper's kind. I thought it's like a cute little ghost! 😂
.
Other rotifers in the video carry eggs, can you spot them? Do you want to hear something weird? Some of the species of the rotifers have only females! Some other species have males when they only need males to fertilize eggs! Males hatch from eggs as deformed, they cannot feed themselves even and before they die they try to fertilize the eggs! It really reminds me some male friends I had in high school. 🤣
.

This is how some species of snake go to bed!
Snakes have no eyelids, so they can never close their eyes or blink. Instead of eyelids, thin clear membrane cover their corneas, called spectacles or brilles. These are attached to their skin. Although they can not close their eyes, they can close the retinas when they are sleeping.

THE NIGHTMARE - By @guybehindstories

It was my first Break-up,
Friends took me to have
alcohol with them.
8 shots then 9 shots and then 10 shots.
They tried to stop me 
but I didn't listen and continued 
drinking.

one of friend who lived beside my house said that he will drop me by.

We reached home I dizzily opened the door and dashed myself to the bed.
Few hour later
I got a nightmare
I was totally broken
 thinking about my relationship

I fear loosing her so much

I'm totally sick figuring out 
how she changed.
It felt like a regret but taking 
deep breath i decided to trust myself 
and though everything will be fine
with a Broken heart.

Then I heard 
Someone whispering
Hey wake-up it 10am
Still you're sleeping.
My eyes halfway open
And I saw
It was just a dream
The Time was 2am midnight
I woke up
and went for a bath
I can hear the voice of shower
while
Standing under it
Feeling low and I
Don't have ability to live more.

I came out
Took a chair and my moms' saree
Tied to fan
In my room
I stood on a chair
hanged myself.
And suddenly I hear a voice
Beta, its already 10am
Don't you want to go college.
I was surprised
How can I hear when there is no one in the room.
I tried opening my eyes 
The light rays of sun
On my eyes
Made my eyes close again.
I tried to wake up
And
I saw mom staring at me,
I was shivering 
She asked me what happened
Are you okay 
I replied with yes
Just a bad nightmare.

And I come to know
Mother is the only person
Who will never leave you alone
In any situation. •

After reading the text, London told the crowd, “I’ve never felt this type of pain before.” “His soul was majestic,” she continued, recalling him playing music for their children and lighting sage each morning so they could start their days off right. DAY DRINKING FTW!
With HOT HOT summer approaching, we can only think of cold cold beers.🍺🍺 So before you decide to go towards the bottomless mimosa direction, we’d like to inform you about beers. And by the end of this Summer, Team MF has decided to make a beer expert out of you. We have decided to dedicate all the coming wednesdays to beer, complete with beer trivia and beer insights!

Before we start, ALL HAIL MID-WEEK DRINKING!

Speaking of which, let’s start with Wit beers,

With high level of wheat, sometimes even oats, this pale and crisp drink is usually layered with spices and aroma like coriander seeds or orange peel. Fruity in taste, this Wit beer sounds healthy to us! 😬

Though Wit beer is available in various brands, we start with *DRUMROLL* Hopper @hopperbelgium . A brand known to us for some time now - it entered the Indian market late in 2018, but we’re glad that at least it’s here. This 100 year old recipe was crafted in the region of Brouwerij De Brabandere in Bavikhove, Belgium - try saying that under 10 seconds! 🙌 Hopper gets its name from the words "Hop on, Hop off" printed on the sides double decker buses in Brussels! 
What makes Hopper Wit so special? It is a beer for non-beer drinkers. Low on bitterness and really smooth, it creates a creamy mouthfeel. This is a brand to start with if you are not a beer person.

Enjoy a Cold One! Happy Drinking! 🍻

✨ Muslim Women You Should Know ✨ 
Arwa al- Sulayhi was born in 1308 in modern day Haraz, Yemen. She was orphaned at a young age and raised by her aunt and uncle, the leader of Yemen. At the age of 17 she married their son and her aunt became her mother in law. When her father in law died, she and her husband became ruler. However, because her husband was bedridden so she reigned as co regent. She was said to have been brave, devout and independent with a great memory for poems, stories, and historical events. Unlike her mother in law, she veiled herself but she still attended mix gender state councils and refused to be hidden behind a screen during private meetings. When her husband died, she remarried in order to remain in power, however legend says she never allowed the marriage to be consummated. During her reign, she sent pilgrims to Gujarat, India to establish Shia communities there, which still exist to this day. Domestically, she worked on expanding her empire, developing roads and building schools and mosques across Yemen. Arwa al-Sulayhi was given the rank of hujja, a prestigious title in Shia Islam, signifying the closest living image of Gods will - the first time a woman was awarded this title. #MuslimWomenYouShouldKnow #Muslimah #femislay #MuslimGirlArmy

Metals are hard, they said🤔
⠀
Indium is a fusible, sparkly, silvery-white metal with a melting point of 157°C (314°F).This temperature is one of the reference points on the international temperature scale. 
It is soft enough to cut with a knife or bend with your hands… or even bite through! If you bend a piece of indium, you will hear a crunch – a testament to changes in the metal’s crystal lattice. Indium ions tint flames indigo. 
German scientists Ferdinand Reich and Jerome Richter discovered indium in 1863. Reich was studying a zinc ore, sphalerite, hoping it would contain a sample of the newfound element thallium. As Reich was colorblind, he asked his colleague Richter to check the spectrum for him. The scientists were surprised: instead of the green line they were expecting, Richter noticed a rich violet-blue line that had not been seen before. Reich and Richter realized that they had found a new element. They called it the Latin word indicum – ""purple"" or ""indigo"". When heated, indium reacts with sulfur, forming indium (III) sulfide. 
It dissolves slowly in nitric acid, forming indium (III) nitrate. 
When indium and gallium touch, they dissolve in each other, forming an alloy that melts at 16°C (61°F). Such alloys are used to substitute for mercury in devices like thermometers. 
Indium first found significant use during World War II, where it was used to coat aircraft bearings. Today, indium tin oxide can be found in LCD-TVs, monitors, and smartphone screens. It is a good electrical conductor that can send signals to individual pixels of the screen without interfering with the light from other pixels. Copper-indium-gallium selenide is used as a material for solar batteries.

Money indeed plays such an important part in people’s lives. However, it is not the most important thing in the world, but then again it is defined to be the main tool to actually help people attain what they want as well as what they need. Money may be valuable, but they’re not the most valuable. Money can basically help you get things that you want and need but money doesn’t buy things that actually matter.
.
Money is central to our lives. Yet money is not of central importance. It has nothing whatsoever to do with the lasting values that make life worth living.
.
A perfect example of this is the late Steve Jobs, the man behind Apple Inc. He earns billions of dollars a year, but then when cancer hits him, no amount of money could actually save his life. Money may indeed be extremely important for people to survive and people who says otherwise are totally believing in something else, but is that really the idea of living? Here is an example of a thing that is more valuable than money.
.
Time
.
Money spent is meaningless, but time spent is priceless.
.
There is no doubt that time is actually way more valuable than money. Simply because, time is something that you give but can never take back, you can never borrow time. Every single minute of the day must be cherish and spent wisely. If you want to waste money then my all means go ahead, you can always earn it back or get it back in any way possible. A time that is properly invested is considered as a fortune.
.
The perfect example of this is the time you spend with your loved ones. The problem with most parents who are so busy making so much money, is that they forget that no amount of money can buy memories with their children. They grow up really fast and each day goes by they would long for their parents’ hugs and kisses. They may be rich when it comes to money, but when it comes to time, they sure are poor.
.
.

Thomas Aquinas was born to a noble family in Italy in 1225. As a young man, he went to study at the University of Naples and there came into contact with a source of knowledge which was just then being rediscovered: that of the Ancient Greek and Roman authors, who had previously been shunned by Christian academics. At university, Aquinas also came under the influence of the Dominicans, a new order of monks who, unlike other groups, believed that they should live in the outside world, rather than a cloister.

Personal finance is something you have to learn. Read below

1. Spend less than you earn. This is why they say "it's not what you make it's what you keep." Anyone can go broke whether you make $50k/year, $100k/year or $1m/year. It's better to build your saving skills when you're making less money. Wherever you are, make sure you start now.

2. Just in case shit hits the fan you want some type of cushion. If you lose your job, your business goes under, or have unexpected expenses without some savings you will miss out on opportunities until you fix it. A bit of savings lets you comfortably take some risks and chase opportunities.

3. Right now is the only time you can take action.

4. If you rely on the government, your accountant or anyone to help your finances you will get nowhere. Everything that happens to your finances is 100% your fault. Adopt this mindset.

5. Pay off high interest debt first or use the debt snowball. Do whatever you prefer as long as you are paying it off!

6. We've all heard the average millionaire has 7 sources of income. But even adding a side hustle or just any second stream can make a life changing difference. Anything is better than 1 income stream.

7. You can learn all the important financial rules and knowledge in a few days. The hard part is staying consistent over many months and years. You need to build the right habits and behaviour so you can control your money long term.

8. Income does not determine your wealth. You need the right mindset to be able to create wealth and also keep it. This is how it all starts unless you inherit money or win the lottery. Even a lot of lottery winners go broke because they don't have the right mindset. 
9. If you don't plan where every dollar will go it will disappear.

10. Once you have decent capital and money flowing in you have to make your money work for you. This means learning how to make your money make more money through things like investing.

11. Follow @NowFuture if you want to take control of your finances.

Understand this: You gotta first do what you hate in order to do what you love, tomorrow.
-
The market doesn't really care about your passion. It cares only about what value you are offering . If your passion is drawing but you can only draw half eye and leg,then sorry but you can't "follow your passion and become wealthy". You have to first do something that will add true value to the market, so that AFTER you can enjoy your freedom, drawing.
-
Plus, "doing what you hate" means taking ALL the necessary steps so as to reach your goal.
For example : If you like business, one day will come that you will have to work an aspect of your business that you don't like. BUT you'll have to do it, because ultimately you like taking care of your business. That's it. Legacy has a price.

Once you're in the sweet spot of the generous present moment, where all possibilities exist in the quantum field, how do you turn one or more of those potentials, those immaterial possibilities, into reality in the three-dimensional world of matter? This requires 2 things: a clear intention and elevated emotion. Your clear intention is exactly what it sounds like- you have to get clear on what it is you want to create, getting as specific as possible, and describe it in detail. Let's say you want to go on a great vacation. Where is it you want to go? How do you want to get there? Who do you want to go with, or who do you want to meet when you're there? What do you want to see when you're there? You get the point. Make it detailed- make it as real as you can. Those thoughts, which make up your intention, are the electrical charge you are sending into the unified field. ⁣
⁣
Now you have to combine that intention with an elevated emotion, such as love, gratitude, inspiration, joy, excitement, awe or wonder to name a few examples. You have to tap into the feeling you anticipate you have when you manifest your intent, and then feel the emotion ahead of the experience. The elevated emotion (which carries a higher energy) is the magnetic charge youre sending out into the field. And when you combine the electric charge (your intention) with the magnetic charge (elevated emotion), you create an electromagnetic signature that is equal to your state of being.✨

⠀
🌱В английском- Spanish (спанишь)⠀
🌱В русском - испанский⠀
🌱В испанском- Español (эспаньол)⠀
🌱В итальянском - Spanolo (спаньоло)⠀
🌱В немецком - Spanisch (шпанишь).
🌱В японском посмотрела - スペイン語 (спэинло) Даже эти иероглифы звучат похоже!!😂⠀
*Если что, последние 2 языка не уверена, чисто по Гугл переводчику ради интереса посмотрела😬⠀
⠀
А теперь такой же разбор с Немецким🧐⠀
🌵В английском- German (джёман)⠀
🌵В русском - Немецкий⠀
🌵В испанском- Alemán (алэман)⠀
🌵В немецком - Deutsch (доичь)⠀
🌵В итальянском- Tedesco (тэдэско) Я угарала!))Тэдэско!!! Не могу, в моей голове это звучит очень смешно😂🙈Будто кто-то кашлянул или чихнул: «Тэдэээээско!» «будь здоров!»😂😂сори, минутка моего юмора😄⠀

This world, is designed in a way to constantly make you feel like you’re not enough. From the beauty industry to class systems to luxury lifestyle blogging and even the most subtle of our deeply injected realities like bank loans, credit cards, mortgage - everything, is designed to 1. Give you a sense of accomplishment... like ‘you belong here’, and 2. That you’re never going to be enough. You’ll be in this cycle, forever.

It’s tricky, it’s messy, and if there’s just one thing you take away from me today... it’s to stand up for yourself.

No matter what you do - never stop standing up for yourself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Even when it feels like it’s you against a hundred, stand up for yourself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When you’re told you’re being difficult and no one behaves the way you do - stand up for yourself. What people do or the kind of things they sign up to is their problem, you do what’s right for you.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Remember that just because ‘everyone’s doing it’ doesn’t mean you have to do it too. That’s peer pressure, it’s bullying, and if it feels wrong, say no.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When they think it’s acceptable to throw things in your face just because it’s a policy, however unfair, you stand up for yourself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When the world is making you feel like you’ve done something wrong and this is your fault - stand up for yourself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When you think they’re being unfair, and you deserve better - stand up for yourself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When you’re expected to do things just because there’s power abuse and you think you don’t have a right - stand up for yourself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When you’re being told to stop standing up for yourself - is when you damn well stand up for yourself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When you feel it in your gut... you better stand up for yourself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Okay? Okay.
Trust me, you may not understand it now, but you won’t regret fighting for your rights.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🌻

I absolutely love my #ToneYBands, they are the perfect tool to add a little zing to my workouts, here are a few exercises you can do with them to tone up your arms while engaging and working your core too.
1. Hip Hinge position: Arm Rockets - 3 sets x 20 reps
2. Hip Hinge position: Arm Circles - 3 sets x 20 reps
3. Hip Hinge position: One arm reaches forward while the other kicks back - 3 sets x 20 reps
4. All Fours: Opp Arm and Leg Reach - 3 sets x 20 reps
5. All Fours: Abduct Opp Arm and Leg - 3 sets x 15 reps.
ToneYBands are available in 3 sizes, I'm using 3/4th pound each, please DM @yasminsbodyimage if you want to buy a pair or ☎ +91 97690 30371

Photo by @rainerblickle || My dad, my brother, and I were driving up from Wellington to Napier on the northern island of New Zealand. We ascended into a hilly area and stopped at a pullout to look at the view. It was too foggy to get any good landscape shots, but the low lying vegetation caught my eye. As I walked back to the car, I snapped a couple shots of these ferns (I think they’re ferns) because I thought they looked nice against the fog and ridge line.
•
Often times, I don’t get to shoot in the perfect light or weather conditions. However, I think if you look hard enough and get creative, you can find something to photograph no matter what. That night, I imported these images into the Lightroom Mobile app. I knew I wanted the orange to pop against the green and blue, and that’s how I ended up with the final edit.

Are humans fit for #space? A new study comparing astronaut Scott Kelly's body while he was in space to his twin brother Mark's body while he was on Earth revealed a stunning amount of changes long-term exposure to spaceflight can cause.

The “Fluids Shifts” experiment was performed by astronaut Scott Kelly when he lived on the ISS from March 27, 2015, to March 1, 2016, the longest spaceflight by an American. At the same time, his twin brother Mark, also an astronaut, tested his intracranial pressure back on Earth.

Long-term exposure to spaceflight is dangerous.  Fluids shift to astronauts’ heads; the left side of their hearts grow. Unless they exercise vigorously, they lose muscle and bone. But only four individuals have lived in space for a year or more. 
Get all the details on what happens to the human body when we're in space (and what the study found in the changes between the two astronaut twins) by clicking the link in our bio. 🎨 by @case_chin

South Korea’s top court ruled that the country’s highly restrictive abortion law is unconstitutional and set a deadline for officials to lift the ban by next year, nearly 70 years since it was enacted. Passed in 1953, the law bans most abortions except in the cases of rape, incest and the life of the mother. It also punishes women who receive abortions, as well as doctors who perform the procedure. In the select cases where abortions are allowed, the woman must seek her spouse’s permission. In a 7-2 ruling Thursday, the judges on the country’s constitutional court said the ban “limits women’s rights to pursue their own destinies, and violates their rights to health by limiting their access to safe and timely procedures,” and ordered the country’s national assembly to pass a new law legalizing abortion by the end of 2020. // 📸: Getty Images ⁣

When you wanna show up to the party with an epic appetizer, it's bound to get a little bit messy. Luckily, NEW Brawny quarter sheets can be used for small counter cleanups or as napkins to avoid cheesy fingers. #TearASquare #Sponsored by @brawnybrand⁣
⁣
PINCHED PIZZA PIE:⁣
2 tubes store-bought pizza dough⁣
1/4 cup marinara sauce⁣
1/4 cup grated mozzarella⁣
16 slices pepperoni⁣
1 egg, beaten⁣
1/4 cup butter, melted⁣
2 cloves garlic, minced⁣
2 tablespoons parsley, minced⁣
STEPS:⁣
Preheat oven to 375 degrees.⁣
Grease an 8-inch pie dish and set aside until ready to use. On a lightly floured wooden surface, gently roll out the pizza dough into a large rectangle and using a standard drinking glass, cut out 15 circles. Spoon 1 teaspoon of marinara sauce in the center of the circle, add a sprinkling of cheese and 1 pepperoni slice. Fold the circles in half to make a semicircle, fold in half again and bring the bottom corners together to create a petal and pinch together.⁣
Place the petals around the edge of the greased pan with the points facing the center and continue until you have reached the center of the dish. Brush with egg wash and bake for 20 minutes.⁣
Meanwhile, in a small bowl whisk together melted butter, minced garlic and minced parsley.⁣
Remove the pie from the oven, brush the top with garlic and parsley mixture and bake for another 5 minutes. Let cool slightly, carefully slide the pie out of the pan onto a serving platter and enjoy!

¿Qué mejor que ver la final de #GameOfThrones con los Huevos de Dragón de Daenerys en tu casa? 🐉⁣⠀
⁣⠀
INGREDIENTES⁣⠀
400 gr. #chocolate semiamargo picado ⁣⠀
400 cc. #crema ⁣⠀
2 tazas #almendras fileteadas ⁣⠀
1 taza glasé verde ⁣⠀
1 taza glasé negro ⁣⠀
1 taza glasé blanco ⁣⠀
c/n polvo dorado para pintar ⁣⠀
c/n polvo verde para pintar ⁣⠀
⁣⠀
PROCEDIMIENTO⁣⠀
En una olla calentar la crema hasta el primer hervor.⁣⠀
Volcar la crema caliente sobre el chocolate picado. Dejar reposar 2 minutos y mezclar.⁣⠀
Enfriar en heladera 2 horas.⁣⠀
Hacer la forma de los huevos de dragón con las manos.⁣⠀
Pinchar las almendras fileteadas en los huevos.⁣⠀
Colocar los huevos sobre una rejilla y bañarlos con el glasé de colores. ⁣⠀
Esperar que se sequen y pintarlos con un pincel con polvo dorado.⁣⠀

How can you get better light in the field? Simple: just get out more. The more time you spend in any given place the more likely you are to experience interesting atmospheric conditions and beautiful light. When I first photographed this beach in New Zealand back in 2012 I committed myself to shooting sunrise and sunset on the beach for 5 days straight. That's 10 opportunities for the light to do something interesting. 10x more chances for better conditions than if I showed up for a single shoot. And if you want to come home with your best possible photos you need to give yourself every opportunity. In this case I was also extremely lucky: the light blew up on sunset #2 for me and I was able to then move on to other locations for more photographs.

Police stopped BJP cadres at places where they took out the rallies. 
The BJP`s West Bengal unit president Dilip Ghosh on Friday had warned the state administration not to obstruct the scheduled rallies and added that if such attempts were made, the ruling Trinamool Congress (TMC) would face the brunt in the election.

Avoid food waste, and follow this simple tip to find out if your eggs are still good to eat.
.
Millions of eggs are wasted because of the "best before" date, even when they are still good to eat!
.
Put your eggs in a bowl with cold water. If the eggs sink to the bottom and lie flat on their sides, they’re very fresh. If they’re less fresh but still good to eat, they’ll stand on one end at the bottom of the bowl. If they float to the surface, they’re no longer fresh enough to eat. Easy! 😉

“A new paper in the scientific journal, Nature, suggests that 45 percent of the land area that nations have so far pledged to allocate for carbon drawdown is being used to for commercial plantations.
There’s a huge difference between restoring natural forests and planting trees for commercial use, for example the large-scale monoculture of oil palms to provide us with the palm oil so ubiquitous in snacks and cosmetics. The latter are less efficient at carbon storage, and in fact release carbon emissions by replacing peatland, as well as being detrimental to wildlife.”

To the Voters of the Nation,

I want to start by asking you a few questions:

Are you going to vote this year? If not, then is it because you're not 18 yet? Or because you don't have your name registered in the Electoral Roll in the first place? Or because you think that your vote doesn't count?

If your answer to either of the last two questions is a Yes, then I have got something to tell you.

1. The Election Commission of India is still accepting applications for new voters in a few Phases. (All the states of the country are distributed into 'phases', based on the Election Dates & Constituencies, for those who do not know). If your resident state falls in any one of them, you can still get yourself registered on the Voter's List and vote this year. More details are available on www.nvsp.in. So go, and do the needful. It's never too late.

2. I know you must have heard this before, but it cannot be stressed enough - EVERY VOTE COUNTS. From a billionaire industrialist's to a grocery shop owner's, to a paddy farmer's. Each vote contributes to the fate of this country, and to what will govern us, for the coming five years. Your voice matters more than you think, and even a single word said can make an ocean's worth of difference. So I urge you to go and exercise the right you've been given, wisely. And I'm not asking you to have a strong stance on the political situation of the country, or even stand by a particular party. Whom you vote for is a secondary concern, what matters more is that you vote in the first place.

Ours is a country built from myriad cultures, people coming from different places, each with a voice that makes a different sound. And each sound is equally worthy of being made. So please, go and vote. I urge you, the youth of the nation, to give a new dimension to the term 'inked'. Tattoos are cool, sure, but there will be nothing more happening than seeing young college kids flaunt their indigo nails, proud of their right to choose. It is time for us to give it back to the country, and be the change we've been demanding to see.

Here's to us, collectively taking our country forward, again.

I will see you at the Poll Booth.

On Instagram , I keep on getting questions like - how is my skin so flawless? How do I maintain it ? How m I so blessed with such good skin ? 
My reaction to all these questions is - 🔔 🤦🏻‍♀️ It takes a lot of time, effort and money to maintain this. My skin care routine is crazy and all those expensive products ! 🙄 still some days my skin doesn’t behave nicely !! I break out every now and then, I have really bad dark circles , redness , as I’m aging , I can see fine lines , wrinkles. What all you see on Instagram is filtered. The idea of being flawless seems nice but isn’t practical . It’s ok to have pimples , dark circles and still love yourself. As long as you are taking good care of your skin, you dont need to worry about bad skin days.  Still I’m going to give some skin tips which might help some you out there - 
1. Eat your veggies, what goes inside shows outside 
2. Try using natural chemical free products on your skin, I apply aloe Vera everyday. I make face masks from things I have in the kitchen , I don’t use these store bought masks.
Also I simple love the products from @herbalicious_official ! There saffron night repair cream and under eye gel is so so amazing !! ( please note this is not a paid collaboration) I genuinely use their products because it’s all natural and chemical free.

This day promise yourself to be healthy physically and mentally (I know we daily do it and break it...but try to keep 😋) It's important to give your body as much importance as you give to your job, money, family etc. It's ok to have less money, to not have the job you always fancied about, to be less successful, to party less ...but it's NOT ok to compromise your health in anyway. So love your body, love your mind, give time to yourself, eat healthy, exercise and remember 'Health is the first wealth.'

I don't have many regrets. ⁣
⁣
But when I look back on my life, I can see one very distinct pattern emerge. ⁣
⁣
Whenever I followed the whims and opinions of the crowd, I lost money, health, happiness, and sanity. ⁣
⁣
When I lost touch with MY mission, MY beliefs, and MY vision, everything in my life fell into chaos. ⁣
⁣
Whether it was launching a product that was in-congruent with my brand and personality (like that stupid cookbook I launched--even though I'd never even turned on the oven in my own apartment), entering into a relationship because I wanted to be accepted and validated (instead of finding someone with whom I was truly connected), or setting goals that weren't aligned with what I truly wanted (because "everyone else was doing it"), following the masses and listening to the opinions of OTHERS over myself always led to failure and regret. ⁣
⁣
This is not to say that you shouldn't learn from those who are wiser than you--you should. And it will likely save you years of pain and regret. ⁣
⁣
Simply that your life is YOUR life. And you must learn to first listen to yourself and what YOU want and what YOU believe before you allow yourself to be influenced by others. ⁣
⁣
Don't waste your life pursuing goals that excite other people or living a lifestyle designed to keep up appearances and feed the ego. ⁣
⁣
Instead, follow YOUR vision. Do the things that excite you, that light you on fire, that fill you with passion--even if no one else understands. ⁣
⁣
Sure, you might fail. ⁣
⁣
But here's the thing...⁣
⁣
At some point in your life, you're going to fail no matter what you do. ⁣
⁣
And it's better to fail in pursuit of your dream and vision than in pursuit of someone else's. ⁣
⁣
So drop a line in the comments below and let me know... ⁣
⁣
What is YOUR vision? What mark do you want to leave on the world? How do you want to be remembered when you're gone?

Phone beeps.
You rush to check the notification.
Slowly sliding down, you realize it wasn't that 
name you hoped.
Hours pass, at regular intervals, 
you constantly check for that one message to come.
It doesn't.

You just had dinner,
you open those old chats,
reading them again, you have a smile
but realize how easily times change.
Just then, you see them online.
You patiently wait, hoping for 'typing' to happen.
It doesn't.

They go offline, another hour passes.
You check back again,
'Online' it shows, fluctuates, 'Online' again.
You hold on, you 'Close all tabs'.
you resist, but maybe how about trying 'Once more'.
You make up your mind, just one last time. That's it!

You type, 'Hey! Supp? :)', anxiously wait, 'Online', the screen indicates.
Minutes pass, they don't reply.
You repeatedly keep on checking.
15 mins - 30 mins - 45 mins.

Finally the phone beeps,
their reply, you try to make it a conversation.
5-10 messages exchanged.
The chat ends, with their promise of texting tomorrow.
You go back to sleep, overthinking, 
overanalyzing, but maybe you tried yet again.
You decide to not drop a message first tomorrow.

Still, you do, the cycle continues.

My dearest princess,

Yeah! Even today you're a little princess for me as you were on the first day when you stepped into this world. I can't believe that this little princess who was always treated as a daughter by me is going to tie her knot tomorrow to her man of dreams. Excited? Anxious? Happy? Sad? I know you're having a mixed feeling over all these things. I still remember the days when we used to play with mom's makeup kit and went to dad to show him who looks prettier, and whenever dad took my name, your beautiful face would turn into a pumpkin within no time. You're the same girl who used to tell me " I hate relationships" after your breakup, you're the same girl who used to scream " I  am not going to marry ever" whenever our relatives used to tease us, you're the same girl who used to fight with me for the last bite of a chocolate, you're the same girl who turned her dreams true and made us proud. And today she's all set to tie the knot. She's going to start a new phase of life. Your naughtiness, excitement, joy everything at one side and the responsibilities which you have to take, your behavior, your self-respect on the other side. Being married doesn't only include a  husband to be with and enjoying your married life happily or raising kids. You have to look after your in-laws, you have to take several responsibilities, you have to present yourself as a good wife, a good daughter in law, a good mother and keep many relations bounded. 
Years before you were Wrapping yourself with mom's saree, applying light makeup, putting a bindi, wearing some bangles, making each flip of your hair count; you used to run around the house in excitement and say " I am the prettiest bride" and we all used to burst into laughter. Tomorrow that prank is going to be in real, and the memories are going to be imprinted in our hearts forever.

Cheers to our togetherness, our fights, our naughtiness, and every single action. We have been with each other every single time; from holding hands to learn how to walk to going school together, sharing dolls , eating in the same plate, sharing the same dresses, using each others...

Trust the eye of the forest at night, for there is none who betrays her sight, all but one who now just might, for he is darker than her night.
.
. Many years ago, it was the winds of Kymara that sent its first chill down The Bison’s spine. A predator was near and whatever it was, waited for darkness before choosing to move. One last glance at the road and in the distance something dark moved, so dark that it looked like it had carved a piece of the night out. Like the shadow of a big cat, it shifted shape and vanished. Little did we know that many moons later, it would make sense.
.
.
 At The Bison, Kymara was known as the land of the tall and twisted trees. Shadow-lands where the undergrowth was darker than the night sky. Lands that need a king true to its habitat and with monsoon clouds of 2014 Kymara was blessed with more than just rain. Like the wind, he was concealed but his presence was felt. He took our world and the forest by storm. He was the shadow of the forest that would soon become the soul. He defied the laws of natural selection and thrived by adapting in the most phenomenal ways. We at The Bison named him ‘Saya’, which meant ‘shadow’ in the local language. .
.
Saya was small, young and sleek. Too small at first to battle the kings so instead, he stole the queens. Cleopatra, Mist and Kate belonged to Scarface and Torn Ears but they had been wood away by the nomadic panther In search of a home. He courted them together and continued to lure more females as he slowly took over parts of the forest that belonged to Scarface and Torn Ears. Torn Eats shifted to an area where newer and younger females lurked but Scarface’s lands were under threat from both Saya and Kismet, the resident tigress. A battle was imminent and it happened on a hot summer afternoon. The next morning Scarface was back in the backwaters and limping. Both were left wounded but they reached an important understanding, at least for now. .
.

Day 2 in Ranthambhore
. 
Still never beaten this image of T24 from several years back. In fact last year, my work was very average.
. 
As many people know T24, after killing his 4th human, was shot with a tranquilliser gun and now lives in an Indian zoo. Ranthambhore misses him.
. 
But he was a man eater and at least he was not killed - as many wanted. That would have been wrong - he did not know he was doing something that put his life in danger.
. 
It’s safety first here therefore. I try everything to get close and we did have a moment after 9 hours today. It’s gruelling work, but the biggest buzz of the lot. We will show the image later this week.
. 
It is humbling that so many Indian photographers are saying hello to me this week. I am flattered as India punches way above its weight in this profession.
